attributes.description: The week's selection of beef & pork recipes

attributes.name: 10-Min Rump Steak, Cheesy Gnocchi & Mushrooms
attributes.description: In just 10 minutes you'll have a fabulous steak dinner inspired by the cuisine of Northern Italy. After cooking the steaks, you'll fry the gnocchi in the same pan to soak up all of the delicious flavours, and cover with grated Italian hard cheese. Served with balsamic-infused mushrooms and spinach on the side.

attributes.name: Teriyaki Chicken Donburi Bowl
attributes.description: Straight from our mouthwatering wagamama menu, you'll top steaming sticky rice with tender teriyaki chicken, shredded carrots and peppery pea shoots – fresh and easy!

attributes.name: Fiery Thai Kaeng Pa With Jumbo Prawns
attributes.description: Heads up, this curry is not for the faint-hearted! Kaeng Pa, or ‘Jungle Curry’, is a broth dish from Thailand made with seriously spicy green and red chilli paste.

attributes.name: 3 Cheese Veg-Packed Pasta Bake
attributes.description: Layer this courgette pasta with not one, but three cheeses for a tasty wholesome midweek bake!

attributes.name: Crispy Pork Khao Soi
attributes.description: We're heading to North Thailand for noodles topped with crispy pork and drenched in coconut red curry sauce. With zesty lime & tons of fresh flavours - khao-nt us in!

attributes.name: Comforting Cottage Pie
attributes.description: The goodness of our cottage pie lies beneath a cheesy mash topping. Beef mince bubbles in rich stock, ramping up the flavour before serving with broccoli.

attributes.name: Roasted Tomato Linguine With Basil & Seed Crumb
attributes.description: Make your own tomato sauce for this plant-based take on an Italian staple. You'll roast a mix of cherry and plum tomatoes and cook them into a rich sauce with onion and garlic. Top it off with a crunchy toasted pine nut & seed pangrattato and fresh basil. Tomatolly simple!

attributes.name: 10-Min Steamed Asian Fish With Brown Rice
attributes.description: This delicious Japanese-inspired meal is so easy to prepare yet packed full of flavour. You'll make a quick miso sauce to steam your fish and green beans in. Served with wholesome brown rice, this one is perfect for a warming weeknight dinner! (Dairy-free: see our FAQs for details.)

attributes.name: 10-Min Spicy Chilli Paneer Noodles
attributes.description: This recipe takes its inspiration from the Indo-Chinese cuisine found in eastern India. You'll cook cubes of paneer with soy sauce, before adding crunchy red peppers and egg noodles. You'll coat it all in a spicy homemade chilli sauce and garnish with a handful of crushed peanuts – all in just 10 mins!

attributes.name: Chicken Tinga Tacos With Lime Mayo
attributes.description: For a taste of Mexico, serve spicy shredded chicken over soft warm tortillas with tangy lime mayo, cheese and crunchy lettuce. Tastes fantas-taco!

attributes.name: Creamy Crab Linguine With Lemon
attributes.description: Enjoy a little bit of luxury with this simple crab linguine. You'll use the brown crab meat and Cornish clotted cream to create a decadent sauce. The dish is finished with a simple but impressive diced tomato garnish (known in the industry as 'concasse'), along with the white crab meat. Gorgeously simple & delicious!

attributes.name: 10-Min Mushroom Bibimbap With Sriracha
attributes.description: Create a veg-filled feast of bold Korean flavours in just minutes with crispy honey, soy & ginger mushrooms over brown rice, sesame spinach, pickled carrot and a runny fried egg on top. Finish with a drizzle of fiery Sriracha sauce!
